body:
Workaround: Change "large-tables" into "32-column-tables" (Or just remove that feature because that's now the new default). @diesel-rs/core As far as I could see this happens because we [deny warning](https://github.com/diesel-rs/diesel/blob/master/diesel/src/lib.rs#L113) in diesel and then drop a warning that we deprecated the large-table feature inside of diesel. So the build will fail. Additionally the error message is really bad. It seems like cargo is hidding the real message because if I use a local diesel clone I get the following message:
Error message

Diesel is an ORM and query builder designed to reduce the boilerplate for database interactions. 4 | | //! I've released 1.2.2 with a short term fix, and opened #1636 to come up with a better long term answer
